THE GAME
--------

  'Bibarr' is a Workbench game that is based on the 'sliding-tile'
type of games, where the goal is to move bars of various colours
so they fall in a cross shape hole that is located at the center
of the game board.

  To move a bar, a neighbouring bar of the same type (or a small
block) must be in line with the bar that is to be moved. The bar
can move either toward the empty space or toward a different type
of bar, if it is located next to the bar to be moved.

  If the bar would move toward a different type of bar, those two
bars will combine to make a cross, and the cross can move toward
the empty space (if it is located next to the cross), whatever the
shape of the neighbouring bars. When a bar move toward another bar
to become a cross, that bar will be replaced by a small octagonal
block. This block can move afterwards if the empty space is next
to it...

  A bar or a cross can fall in the hole if it is not already
occupied, and is in line with the bar or the cross. When a bar or
cross falls in the hole, it is replaced by a small block.

  A peculiarity about the game is that the number of moves made
decreases by 25, any time a cross with two bars of the same colour
fall in the hole... Why not?!

  If you get stuck in the game, you can click on the 'New Game'
button to start over, but be aware that the amount of moves you
make for the current game is added up until you complete it...

  Complete the game in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

